
There are numerous ways set up to run these tests. This document provides some common examples



If you want to run the test on a Selenium Grid running on Ubuntu, fill out the following
(note that seleniumHub needs to have the unique grid Url in order to work. The below is just an example):
     seleniumEnvironment:hub
     browser:Chrome
     browserVersion:
     platform:Ubuntu
     platformVersion:
     seleniumHub:http://192.168.99.100:4444/wd/hub
     browserstackResolution:
     browserstackUsername:
     browserstackPassword:
     browserstackProject:
     browserstackBuild:
     baseUrl:https://easierautomation.wordpress.com


To run the tests locally on a Windows computer, enter the following:
     seleniumEnvironment:local
     browser:Chrome
     browserVersion:
     platform:Windows
     platformVersion:
     seleniumHub:
     browserstackResolution:
     browserstackUsername:
     browserstackPassword:
     browserstackProject:
     browserstackBuild:
     baseUrl:https://easierautomation.wordpress.com